message.content:
cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with 3D human pose estimation from 2D images using CNNs. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics) is also a likely category as the paper proposes an image-based synthesis engine to generate synthetic images of humans with 3D pose annotations. 
3. cs.RO (Robotics) is another possible category as the paper uses 3D Motion Capture (MoCap) data to augment the real images with 2D human pose annotations. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with generating photorealistic synthetic images of humans. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper uses an end-to-end CNN for full-body 3D pose estimation and tackles pose estimation as a K-way classification problem.
